{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_25","type":"reasoning","text":"**Analyzing key issues**\n\nI’m considering that many screens might be broken with the KEY_ENTER function. The user specified they want to address one issue at a time, prioritizing the highest concern. It seems like the button could be causing crashes when selecting user/login, and selecting media might lead to endless loading. This could be due to overlays capturing keys or losing focus. I think I need to inspect the unified-controller mapping to see if we can adapt by supporting Key.Enter across UI key handlers.\n**Investigating loading issues**\n\nI’m considering if the loading issue is due to pressing A on the home screen, which may trigger both item selection and an overlay. I want to inspect the app's logic for navigating to detail views and think the loading might hang if the load_item_detail process is slow because of large image files being loaded sequentially.\n\nIt also occurs to me that the image cache might not be using a timeout in the main function, possibly causing requests to hang. I should take a closer look at how the image caching works in the code."}}
